  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `tg version 2021.05.1-alpha`\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nWhen trying to retrieve a transaction by its transaction hash, and that transaction is a pending transaction provided by the `rpcdaemon`, the transaction details should be returned.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nPending transaction subscription works properly and provides a continuous flow of pending transactions, but all calls to `eth_getTransaction` are returning `null`.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n```\r\nmkdir reproduction\r\ncd reproduction\r\nnpm install ethers\r\n```\r\n\r\nin `index.js`:\r\n```\r\nconst ethers = require('ethers');\r\n\r\nconst provider = new ethers.providers.WebSocketProvider('ws://127.0.0.1:8545');\r\n\r\nconst main = async () => {\r\n        provider.on('pending', async (txhash) => {\r\n                console.log(txhash);\r\n                const tx = await provider.getTransaction(txhash);\r\n                console.log(tx);\r\n        });\r\n}\r\n\r\nmain();\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou should see a lot of transaction hashes, but only null values for the `provider.getTransaction(txhash)` call.\r\n",
